Creating a simple OS X App in Python (PyObjC, Cocoa, XIB)
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=N4Q8u7ajGuA
uses Apple's py2applet tool thus:
/System/Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/Current/Extras/bin/py2applet --make-setup Otto.py


installing a local version of python for py2app to bundle up in an app:

# https://gist.github.com/pithyless/1208841
$ brew install --universal readline sqlite gdbm
$ brew install python --universal --framework

$ cd /usr/local
$ virtualenv otto
$ cd otto
$ . activate

$ brew install libtiff libjpeg webp littlecms
#$ pip install yolk  # perhaps use pip list instead
$ pip install Pillow
$ pip install mutagen
$ pip install chardet
$ pip install pymongo
x bson  # don't! pymongo does it, if you do it too it breaks??
$ pip install pyobjc  # damn that takes a long, long time


